  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate family-led interventions for Intensive Care Unit
      (ICU) patients' symptoms (i.e., pain and thirst) that will involve ICU patients' family
      members in the non-pharmacological management of these symptoms. This family involvement may
      help to ameliorate not only patients' symptoms but also the families' symptoms and promote
      family satisfaction with ICU care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
